title: U.S. Consumer Price Index excluding food and energy 1990 to 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Consumer Price Index (100=1982-1984). In total the number of data points it has is 30.
In general Consumer Price Index (100=1982-1984) has rose over the Year.
Consumer Price Index (100=1982-1984) is gradually increasing from 1990 to 2008, roughly constant from 2008 to 2010, and finally slightly increasing from 2010 to 2019.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 1990 and 1991.
The highest Consumer Price Index (100=1982-1984), of value 263.21 was reached at Year 2019
The lowest Consumer Price Index (100=1982-1984), of value 135.5 was reported at Year 1990
